## Context
PRs #702 and #705 added GPU-vectorized and CPU-parallel null model
permutation testing.  The code is merged and validated on real data
(3h → 7min), but the documentation doesn't reflect the new pipeline
capabilities: architecture.md, technical-report.qmd, and handoff docs
are silent on GPU/parallel null models.

## Actions
1. Update `.claude/rules/architecture.md` Phase 2 rules to mention
   null model acceleration (GPU for S2/S1, precomputed TF-IDF for L1,
   joblib for citation methods).
2. Add `--n-jobs` / `NJOBS` to the Makefile documentation in architecture.md.
3. Update `docs/handoff-padme-divergence.md` to include null model
   parallelism alongside divergence GPU notes.
4. Add a paragraph to the technical report methods section explaining
   the permutation test implementation (precomputed distance matrix,
   parallel across windows).

## Test
`grep -c 'n.jobs\|NJOBS\|GPU.*null\|parallel.*permut' .claude/rules/architecture.md` returns ≥ 1.

## Exit criteria
Architecture.md mentions null model acceleration strategy.
Technical report methods section describes permutation test implementation.
Handoff doc covers null model parallelism.
